---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Town Home Schoolhouse | Faith-Based Homeschool Enrichment">
	<section class="relative min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden bg-wood">
		<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-rustic-900/25"></div>
		<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_left,rgba(255,255,255,0.24),transparent_22%),radial-gradient(circle_at_60%_20%,rgba(255,255,255,0.16),transparent_20%)] opacity-90"></div>
		<div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center px-6 py-28 paper-panel rounded-[3rem]">
			<p class="mb-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-rustic-700 bg-rustic-900/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-rustic-700">
				One-Room Schoolhouse
			</p>
			<!-- Crest Logo -->
			<img src="/images/Crest (2).png" alt="Town Home Schoolhouse Crest" class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-6 border-2 border-rustic-600" />
			<h1 class="text-6xl md:text-7xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-900 mb-4 tracking-[0.08em]">
				Town Home
			</h1>
			<h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif text-rustic-700 mb-6">
				Schoolhouse
			</h2>
			<p class="text-xl text-rustic-700 max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-8 leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
				A warm, hand-built learning space where faith, knowledge, and character are cultivated like an old-fashioned school story.
			</p>
			<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center mt-12">
				<a href="#programs" class="bg-rustic-700 text-rustic-50 px-10 py-4 rounded-full font-semibold hover:bg-rustic-600 transition text-lg ring-1 ring-rustic-900/20">
					View Programs
				</a>
				<a href="#contact" class="bg-rustic-100 border-2 border-rustic-700 text-rustic-800 px-10 py-4 rounded-full font-semibold hover:bg-rustic-200 transition text-lg">
					Contact Us
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="absolute bottom-8 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 text-rustic-300 animate-bounce">
			<svg class="w-8 h-8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
				<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 14l-7 7m0 0l-7-7m7 7V3"></path>
			</svg>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Content Divider -->
	<div class="py-12 bg-rustic-100 flex justify-center">
		<div class="w-32 h-16 bg-rustic-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 font-serif text-sm">
			Content Divider Placeholder
		</div>
	</div>

	<section class="py-24 px-6 bg-rustic-50">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
			<div class="paper-panel p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-rustic-300">
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-800 mb-8">Mission & Vision</h2>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					To enrich the homeschool journey by building faith, knowledge, and character in a 
					high-energy, interactive environment that fosters genuine camaraderie and a lifelong love of discovery. 
					Rooted in the counsel of Paul in Philippians 4:8, our goal at Town Home Schoolhouse is to 
					cultivate an edifying educational atmosphere focused on things that are pure, lovely, virtuous, and praiseworthy.
				</p>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-8 leading-relaxed">
					We strive to provide homeschool families with a socially interactive and sensory-engaging space 
					that strengthens a child's confidence, fosters critical thinking, and supports their holistic growth.
				</p>
				<p class="text-rustic-600 italic border-l-4 border-rustic-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-rustic-50">
					"...whatever things are true, whatever things are noble, whatever things are just, 
					whatever things are pure, whatever things are lovely, whatever things are of good report..." 
					<strong>— Philippians 4:8</strong>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Content Divider -->
	<div class="py-12 bg-rustic-200 flex justify-center">
		<div class="w-40 h-20 bg-rustic-300 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-700 font-serif text-sm">
			Ornate Divider Placeholder
		</div>
	</div>

	<section id="about" class="py-24 px-6 bg-rustic-200">
		<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
				<div class="relative">
					<img 
						src="/images/title.png"
						alt="Title" 
						class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl w-full"
					/>
					<div class="absolute -bottom-4 -right-4 w-full h-full border-4 border-rustic-600 rounded-lg -z-10"></div>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-900 mb-6">A Small Classroom with a Big Purpose</h2>
					<p class="text-rustic-700 mb-6 text-lg">
						At Town Home Schoolhouse, we intentionally limit our class sizes to 12 to 14 students. This purposeful design allows us to step away from an institutional feel and cultivate a close-knit, family-like atmosphere where true friendships take root and families build lasting community.
					</p>
					<p class="text-rustic-700 mb-6 text-lg">
						Because we view every child as a unique creation designed by God, our approach extends far beyond academic instruction. A smaller, intimate setting gives our teachers the freedom to truly know each student, allowing us to gently guide their character and nurture their inner growth. We practice kindness, patience, and respect daily—not merely as classroom rules, but as a way to honor God and reflect His love to one another.
					</p>
					<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg">
						Ultimately, we believe that children flourish academically when their spiritual and emotional needs are also being met. By nurturing both the mind and the spirit, we provide a safe, encouraging space where students can confidently grow in their knowledge, understand their God-given value, and walk boldly in His ways.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- About Us -->
	<section class="py-24 px-6 bg-rustic-200">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-900 mb-8">About Us</h2>
			<div class="paper-panel p-12 rounded-[2rem] mb-12">
				<!-- Family Photo -->
				<img src="/images/JulietFamily.png" alt="Townzen Family" class="w-128 h-96 mx-auto mb-8 border-4 border-rustic-600 object-cover" />
				<!-- School Supplies Decorations -->
				<div class="flex justify-center gap-4 mb-8">
					<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-rustic-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 text-xs">📚</div>
					<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-rustic-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 text-xs">✏️</div>
					<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-rustic-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 text-xs">📝</div>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-800 mb-6">Meet the Townzen Family</h3>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					We are a close-knit family of five, along with our beloved mini-farm of animals. Blessed with a wonderful husband since 2007, I am a proud mother to three wonderful children whose age range spans ten years. Our family life is centered around faith, learning, and the unique, multifaceted dynamic of managing both our home and our small, beloved menagerie.
				</p>
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-800 mb-6">Meet Mrs. Juliet</h3>
				<!-- Placeholder for Mrs. Juliet's photo -->
				<div class="w-32 h-32 bg-rustic-300 rounded-full mx-auto mb-6 flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 font-serif text-sm">
					Mrs. Juliet Photo Placeholder
				</div>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					My life is deeply rooted in my faith, which is my central guiding principle and first true passion. I am dedicated to loving the Lord God, diving deep into His Word, and joyfully sharing the unconditional love of Jesus with others. It is my heart's desire to play an active role in growing the Kingdom of God, ensuring His love is reflected in everything I do.
				</p>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					My other greatest passions are family and teaching. I bring over 27 years of diverse educational experience to my role at the Town Home Schoolhouse. My teaching journey encompasses a long career in teaching dance, co-owning and operating Rowe Performing Arts with my mother, and, over the last seven-plus years, homeschooling my own children. For me, educating children is a pursuit I have always held dear. Following my mother's retirement in 2020, I made the prayful decision to become a full-time stay-at-home homeschooling mom and wife.
				</p>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					As a passionate advocate for Christian education, my perspective is shaped by my own background attending Christian school and being homeschooled. My personal journey with dyslexia has fostered an incredibly strong and specific passion for creative, audible, and multisensory learning. It is my goal to ensure every child finds joy and connection in discovery.
				</p>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
					When I am not in the classroom or caring for my family, my hobbies reflect my love for creative expression. I enjoy singing on the praise and worship team, writing short stories and poems, cooking, and finding artistic fulfillment through painting and sewing.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Content Divider with School Supplies -->
	<div class="py-16 bg-rustic-100 flex justify-center items-center gap-8">
		<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-rustic-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 text-2xl">📖</div>
		<div class="w-20 h-12 bg-rustic-300 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-700 font-serif text-sm">
			School Supplies Divider
		</div>
		<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-rustic-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600 text-2xl">🖍️</div>
	</div>

	<!-- Programs Overview -->
	<section id="programs" class="py-24 px-6 bg-rustic-100">
		<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
			<!-- School Supplies Accents -->
			<div class="flex justify-center items-center gap-6 mb-8">
				<div class="w-10 h-10 bg-rustic-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600">📏</div>
				<h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-center text-rustic-900">Our Programs</h2>
				<div class="w-10 h-10 bg-rustic-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-rustic-600">🧮</div>
			</div>
			<p class="text-center text-rustic-600 mb-4 text-lg">
				Once-a-week classes for ages 6–18
			</p>
			<p class="text-center text-rustic-700 mb-16">
				Hands-on learning through movement, teamwork, and creative application.
			</p>
			
			<!-- Younger Students - Ages 6-10 -->
			<div class="mb-16">
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rustic-800 mb-8 text-center bg-rustic-200 inline-block px-8 py-2 rounded-full mx-auto">
					Ages 6–10 | Tuesdays
				</h3>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<!-- PPC Phonics -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									PPC - Phonics, Comprehension & Creativity
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Tuesdays 1:00 PM – 2:00 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$30/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Strengthening reading skills through multi-sensory approach—active play, storytelling, and hands-on crafts.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Phonics Rules</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Reading Comprehension</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Storytelling</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Creative Crafts</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<!-- Math Madness 6-10 -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									Math Madness
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Tuesdays 2:00 PM – 3:00 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$30/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Energetic, multi-sensory math—movement, teamwork, and creative play to build foundational skills.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Real-World Math</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Math Relays</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Team Challenges</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Mnemonic Devices</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<!-- Home Ec & Ag 6-10 -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									Home Economics & Agriculture
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Tuesdays 3:00 PM – 5:00 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$60/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Mastering essential life skills through practical, hands-on application—outdoors and indoors.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Cooking & Preservation</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Sewing & Textiles</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Gardening</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Basic Woodworking</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Older Students - Ages 10-18 -->
			<div class="mb-16">
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rustic-800 mb-8 text-center bg-rustic-300 inline-block px-8 py-2 rounded-full mx-auto">
					Ages 10–18 | Thursdays
				</h3>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<!-- Writing, Debate & Storytelling -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									Writing, Debate & Storytelling
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Thursdays 12:45 PM – 2:30 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$50/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Comprehensive language arts—IEW-style writing, structured debate, and compelling storytelling.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Writing Foundations</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Stylistic Techniques</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Structured Debate</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Public Speaking</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<!-- Math Madness 10-18 -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									 Math Madness
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Thursdays 2:30 PM – 3:15 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$25/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Dynamic, interactive math—movement, strategic teamwork, and hands-on application.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Financial Literacy</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Budget & Interest</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Logic Scavenger Hunts</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Math Tournaments</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<!-- U.S. Geography -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									U.S. Geography: Fun & Games
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Thursdays 3:15 PM – 4:00 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$25/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Interactive geography—mapping, state quizzes, and competitive gameplay across the 50 states.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">States & Capitals</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">History & Culture</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Interactive Mapping</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">State Notebooks</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<!-- Home Ec & Ag 10-18 -->
					<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition">
						<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between mb-4">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-rustic-800 flex items-center gap-2">
									Home Economics & Agriculture
								</h4>
								<p class="text-rustic-500 text-sm mt-1">Thursdays 4:00 PM – 6:00 PM</p>
							</div>
							<span class="bg-rustic-500 text-white px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mt-2 md:mt-0">$60/month</span>
						</div>
						<p class="text-rustic-600 mb-4">Mastering essential life skills through practical application and independent problem-solving.</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Culinary Science</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Machine & Hand Sewing</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Carpentry Projects</span>
							<span class="bg-rustic-100 text-rustic-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs">Financial Literacy</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Our Approach - Rustic Box -->
			<div class="bg-rustic-800 text-rustic-100 p-12 rounded-lg">
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rustic-200 mb-8 text-center">Our Approach</h3>
				<p class="text-rustic-300 text-center mb-8 text-lg">
					Town Home Schoolhouse is designed to support and strengthen the homeschooling family by offering specialized, once-a-week extracurricular enhancements rather than a comprehensive core curriculum. Serving students from ages 6 through 18, our carefully selected classes bridge the gap between high-energy application and focused desk work, bringing learning to life through movement, teamwork, and hands-on application.
				</p>
				<p class="text-rustic-300 text-center mb-8 text-lg">
					Our desire is to strengthen a child's knowledge, understanding, and confidence by providing a fun, interactive learning environment that fosters critical thinking, collaborative social interaction, and a lifelong love of discovery.
				</p>
				<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
					<div class="text-center bg-rustic-700 p-6 rounded">
						<h4 class="font-bold text-rustic-200 mb-2">Multi-Sensory & Active</h4>
						<p class="text-rustic-400">We step away from the traditional desk environment. Students participate in mock stores, whiteboard relays, seed-to-table gardening, and tactical crafts to make learning memorable.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="text-center bg-rustic-700 p-6 rounded">
						<h4 class="font-bold text-rustic-200 mb-2">Structured for Connection</h4>
						<p class="text-rustic-400">To ensure a smooth transition between sessions and provide valuable outdoor socialization, each class concludes with a 10-minute recess and snack break.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="text-center bg-rustic-700 p-6 rounded">
						<h4 class="font-bold text-rustic-200 mb-2">Family-Focused</h4>
						<p class="text-rustic-400">We are committed to supporting entire families in their homeschool journey. We proudly offer a sibling discount—the first child's tuition is full price, and each additional sibling receives a 10% discount.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Registration and Enrollment -->
	<section class="py-24 px-6 bg-rustic-50">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-center text-rustic-900 mb-8">Registration and Enrollment</h2>
			<div class="paper-panel p-12 rounded-[2rem]">
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					Welcome to Town Home Schoolhouse! We offer full Fall and Spring semester classes and are excited to partner with your family to provide engaging, hands-on learning that brings knowledge to life.
				</p>
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-rustic-800 mb-6">How to Enroll:</h3>
				<p class="text-rustic-700 text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					To ensure a wonderful, interactive experience for every student, our class sizes are intentionally kept small. To reserve a space for your child, please reach out to us at:
				</p>
				<div class="bg-rustic-100 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
					<p class="text-rustic-800 font-semibold mb-2">Email: <a href="mailto:townhomeschoolhouse@gmail.com" class="text-rustic-600 hover:text-rustic-500">townhomeschoolhouse@gmail.com</a></p>
					<p class="text-rustic-800 font-semibold mb-2">Phone/Text: (903) 754-8991</p>
